<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aston Villa have confirmed the £19million signing of Lyon forward Bertrand Traore.</p>

<p>The 25-year-old has signed a three-year contract at Villa Park and is the club's fourth major arrival of the summer to take their total spend to £84m.</p>

<p>Dean Smith said: 'We're delighted that Bertrand has chosen to come to Villa. He's a player with immense talent who will really enhance our attacking options.'</p>

<p>Aston Villa have signed Traore from Lyon for £19million as their summer spending continues</p>

<p>Traore played 35 matches last season, mainly on the right wing, and scored four goals, adding five assists. </p>

<p>More to follow</p>
